From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Sat, 12 Jul 2026 23:20:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Wire GRX-019 fused_post_chain runtime resource binding with native
 D3D12 resource handle mapping

Stacked on 0001..0026 + 0036. This is the GRX-019 runtime resource binding
slice (the GRX-009 0005+0007 layers merged into one patch for the
fused_post_chain pass): it lets the Godot fusion-first call site pass the REAL
fused binding to the Rurix bridge so the fail-closed FusedPostChainGate can
validate it, while the runtime stays fallback-first.

- drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h: D3D12Hooks::try_record_fused_post_chain() now
  carries the fused binding: five real D3D12 ID3D12Resource* native handles
  (resolved through RenderingDevice::get_driver_resource, not logical Godot RID
  ids) for src_color/lum_source/prev_luminance/dst_color/dst_luminance, the
  source and lum-source dimensions, and the eight b0 root-constant f32 scalars.
- renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp fusion-first block: resolves the HDR internal
  color texture (src_color) and the LDR tonemap destination (dst_color) native
  handles. The fused luminance segment's distinct <=8x8 reduce level and
  double-buffered 1x1 prev/dst luminance targets are NOT exposed by the public
  Luminance API at this call site, so as a SCAFFOLD the single publicly
  available 1x1 current luminance buffer is bound to lum_source and
  prev_luminance (read-only) and the LDR tonemap destination (fully overwritten
  by the native tonemapper continuation) is bound to dst_color and dst_luminance.
  A distinct, correct fused binding needs the deferred Luminance-API extension /
  draw_graph route B (PASS_CONTRACT.md 3.4/5). When RenderingDevice is
  unavailable or any handle resolves to 0 the call site keeps the native chain.
- modules/rurix_accel: the RurixAccelD3D12Hooks override marshals five
  RXGD_RESOURCE_TEXTURE records (SRV t0..t2 then UAV u0..u1) and the 64-byte b0
  root constant block ([i64 source_width, i64 source_height, i64 lum_source_width,
  i64 lum_source_height, then eight f32 scalars]) into rxgd_record_pass, with a
  zero-native-handle guard that returns false (native fallback).

This is not a real GPU pass: the default record path never returns OK for
RXGD_PASS_FUSED_POST_CHAIN, no D3D12 dispatch is recorded by the shipping
(feature-off) bridge, the per-pass setting defaults to false, the native Godot
luminance_reduction + tonemap chain stays active, and no visual diff, measured
telemetry, or performance claim is made.
---
diff --git a/drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h b/drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h
index 36dbcc1..fc1b44c 100644
--- a/drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h
+++ b/drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h
@@ -124,10 +124,16 @@ public:
 	// this (or the absence of a hooks singleton) keep the native Godot cluster
 	// store path.
 	virtual bool try_record_cluster_store(uint64_t p_cluster_render_native_handle, uint64_t p_render_elements_native_handle, uint64_t p_cluster_store_native_handle, uint32_t p_cluster_render_size_bytes, uint32_t p_render_elements_size_bytes, uint32_t p_cluster_store_size_bytes, const uint8_t *p_push_constants, uint32_t p_push_constant_bytes) { return false; }
-	// GRX-019: opt-in hook for the fused_post_chain pass (fused luminance
-	// final level + tonemap). The base implementation returns false so any
-	// hooks that do not override this (or the absence of a hooks singleton)
-	// keep the native Godot luminance_reduction + tonemap chain.
-	virtual bool try_record_fused_post_chain() { return false; }
+	// GRX-019 runtime resource binding: native resource handle mapping hook
+	// for the fused_post_chain pass (0005/0007-level wiring in one slice). The
+	// caller passes the real D3D12 ID3D12Resource* native handles (resolved
+	// through RenderingDevice::get_driver_resource, not logical Godot RID ids)
+	// for the five fused textures (src_color SRV t0, lum_source SRV t1,
+	// prev_luminance SRV t2, dst_color UAV u0, dst_luminance UAV u1), the
+	// source/lum-source dimensions, and the 64-byte b0 root constant scalars
+	// so the bridge can validate the binding contract and bind real resources.
+	// The base implementation returns false so any hooks that do not override
+	// this (or the absence of a hooks singleton) keep the native Godot chain.
+	virtual bool try_record_fused_post_chain(uint64_t p_src_color_native_handle, uint64_t p_lum_source_native_handle, uint64_t p_prev_luminance_native_handle, uint64_t p_dst_color_native_handle, uint64_t p_dst_luminance_native_handle, uint32_t p_source_width, uint32_t p_source_height, uint32_t p_lum_source_width, uint32_t p_lum_source_height, float p_max_luminance, float p_min_luminance, float p_exposure_adjust, float p_exposure, float p_white, float p_luminance_multiplier, float p_first_frame, float p_auto_exposure_scale) { return false; }
 	static D3D12Hooks *get_singleton() { return singleton; }
 };
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
index 53aba6a..4c73603 100644
